data.text:
Dec. 18—Trae Davis and Brett Wells of Troup High School have received superlative honors on the All-9-3A-II football team, following a vote of the league's head coaches.

Davis, a senior, who is expected to sign a National Letter of Intent with Kansas State University Tuesday morning, was named as the loop's Most Valuable Player.

Wells, a freshman, was picked as the Defensive Newcomer of the Year for his play at outside linebacker.

Wells also earned first team accolades at running back.

The Tigers, who are coached by Sam Wells, had seven offensive players, four defenders and one from special teams named as first team selections.

Junior Bryce Wallum was a first team choice at wide receiver, cornerback and placekicker.

Troup Tiger Football All-9-3A-II award winners

Most Valuable Player — Trae Davis, Sr., WR

Defensive Newcomer of the Year — Brett Wells, Fr., OLB
